misconceptions.student_thought_process:
The student believes that indentation determines which `if` an `else` belongs to. They think the code under `else if (grade >= 60)` is effectively

```java
else if (grade >= 60) {
    if (grade >= 65)
        System.out.println("Letter grade: D");
    else
        System.out.println("Letter grade: F");
}
```

So they expect that any grade ≥ 60 will enter this block: grades 65–69 will print D, and grades 60–64 will print F. They likely also assume that grades below 60 will be handled by some `else` in the chain or that the chain is implicitly exhaustive, so they do not notice that `< 60` prints nothing.
